young actress continued to cast off her youthful image from the Addams Family movies and made a big splash on the independent movie scene, especially in this scathingly witty comedy in which Ricci has the central role. Here she plays Dedee, a buxom, sexually precocious teenager who\'s pregnant, cynical, and looking for a volunteer father for her unborn child. This takes her to the home of her gay half-brother (Martin Donovan) whose current lover (Ivan Sergei) becomes Dedee\'s latest target for seduction. That\'s just the start of the mischief that Dedee so masterfully orchestrates, and Lisa Kudrow (from TV\'s Friends ) is also on hand to deliver some of the movie\'s most quotable dialogue while fending off the affection of a local policeman played by Lyle Lovett. If all this sounds rather sordid, rest assured that the movie\'s got a warm heart (well, sort of) beating beneath all of its sharp-edged sarcasm. Writer-director Don Roos ( Single White Female ) injects most of the movie\'s appeal and humour through Dedee\'s voice-over narration, which constantly reminds us that even the most familiar movie clich�s can be cleverly overturned. As a result, The Opposite of Sex is the opposite of boring. --Jeff Shannon.</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"521\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \">\n    <subfield code=\"a\">Suitable for 18 years and over.</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"538\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \">\n    <subfield code=\"a\">PAL.</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"700\" ind1=\"1\" ind2=\" \">\n    <subfield code=\"a\">Ricci, Christina.</subfield>\n    <subfield code=\"9\">5605</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"700\" ind1=\"1\" ind2=\" \">\n    <subfield code=\"a\">Donovan, Martin.</subfield>\n    <subfield code=\"9\">5606</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"700\" ind1=\"1\" ind2=\" \">\n    <subfield code=\"a\">Kudrow, Lisa.</subfield>\n    <subfield code=\"9\">5607</subfield>\n  </datafield>\n  <datafield tag=\"70